criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Cerebellar ataxia

          -  Ages: 18 to 65 years;

          -  Gender: Both;

          -  Score ≥ 3 and < 8 in subscore of gait in the Scale for the Assessment and Rating of
             Ataxia

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Individuals with other neurological disorders, postural hypotension, vestibular,
             visual, cardiovascular or musculoskeletal disorders that affect the performance of the
             proposed tests;

          -  Pacemaker;

          -  History of seizures;

          -  Metallic implants in the head or neck;

          -  Medication change during the period of study
